      • findReplacement

        private BinaryTree.Node<E> findReplacement​(BinaryTree.Node<E> node)
        Function to find a replacement for a node that is being deleted from a binary search tree. If the node has a null child, then the replacement is the other child. If neither are null, then the replacement is the largest value less than the item being removed.

        Pre : node is not null

        a node is deleted from the tree

        Parameters:
        node - The node to be deleted or replaced
        Returns:
        null if both of node's children are null node.left if node.right is null node.right if node.left is null modified copy of node with its data field changed
